node.text:
@watch.the.f_ with some crazy shots unveiled their first luxury t-shirt collection inspired by the hottest timepieces on market! Here you can see the Rolex GMT Master II with jubilee bracelet inside a Chicken McNuggets box with sauces on it. The collection is NOW AVAILABLE on their official website accessible directly from their IG profile. Go and check them out! #WatchTheF

node.text:
@sergioramos of Paris Saint-Germain, considered one of the all-time greatest defenders in the world, in his latest post was wearing a @patekphilippe Nautilus 5740 Perpetual Calendar in 18k white gold. Introduced as the first grand complication watch in the Nautilus collection, it features a a blue sunburst dial with gold applied hour markers with luminescent coating. #PatekPhilippe

Retail price: $ 124,070.00
Market price: $ 250,000.00

Photo: @sergioramos | @patekphilippe

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Manhattan, New York with @jbalvin, and @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch and text that says '기'.

node.text:
@jbalvin enjoying his one-off @jacobandco Astronomia ‘J Balvin’ set with colored sapphires and diamonds.  This bespoke masterpiece features a 18k white gold case set with baguette-cut diamonds on lugs. The dial is set with 133 triangle-cut colored sapphires totaling 7.83 carats. Above this layer of colorful gems is the iconic Astronomia vertical four-arm movement with four exclusive complications. #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 1 piece
Retail price: $ 1,000,000.00

Photo: @jbalvin | @jacobandCo

node.text:
The founder of Off-White and artistic director of Louis Vuitton @virgilabloh wears a @patekphilippe Nautilus 5711 in stainless steel with custom steel-like dial. The American designer combined his passion for watches with his design creativity to make his bespoke Nautilus. One of the details you can see on the dial is the writing "Patek Philippe" with his Off-White style. This watch was made exclusively for him by the Paris based watch customization company MAD Paris. #PatekPhilippe

Photo: @virgilabloh | @insaneluxurylife

node.text:
@skeletonconceptofficial just unveiled a new version of the Samuel Eto’o Concept 2.0 in 18k yellow gold, made in partnership with the football legend Eto’o himself. The carbon bezel and the gold bracelet accentuates the beautiful skeleton design of the movement. The sub dials numbers are colored in yellow, red and green to remind the Cameroon’s flag where the footballer comes from. The polishing of the external parts of the gold case and the sides of the case required meticulous attention from the master watchmakers. #SkeletonConcept
 
Photo: @skeletonconceptofficial

node.text:
The Prince of Qatar and president of the Qatar Olympic Committee @jo3an during the Olympic Games of Tokyo 2020 was wearing a @patekphilippe Nautilus 5711/1300A in stainless steel with green dial and baguette-cut diamonds, one of the most desirable watches by Patek Philippe collectors. This timepiece replaced the iconic blue 5711 in the final year of production of this reference, and this version is additionally set with 32 baguette-cut diamonds on bezel. This exclusive edition has been introduced in 2021, for the first time a stainless steel Nautilus 5711 has been combined with diamonds. #PatekPhilippe

Retail price : $94,642.00
Market price : $525,000.00

Photo: @qatar_olympic | @patekphilippe

node.text:
@platinumtimesco has now available a special Richard Mille RM011 ‘Felipe Massa’ Automatic Chronograph made by AET, a German based brand that customize Richard Mille and Rolex watches in the highest quality. This masterpiece is made in sapphire, which is the most expensive material made by RM, and it features a colorful dial with pink strap. This version is a limited edition of 3 pieces in pink and but is also available in green and yellow limited to 3 pieces each. #RichardMille

Photo: @platinumtimesco

node.text:
@erling.haaland of Borussia Dortmund ahead of a pre-season match wears another @rolex GMT-Master II 126719 BLRO in 18k white gold with a special ‘Meteorite’ dial. It features the classic GMT Master II bidirectional rotatable 24-hour graduated bezel in red and blue. This timepiece has been introduced at Baselworld 2019 as the first GMT Master fitted with meteorite dial. #Rolex

Retail price: $ 39,230.00
Market price: $ 67,500.00

Photo: @blackyellow | @rolex

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by INSANE LUXURY on July 24, 2021 tagging @watchanalytics. May be an image of wrist watch and text.

node.text:
After the EURO 2020 victory of Italy National Team it has been interesting to analyze the trend of the @richardmille released in partnership with Italy’s Coach @mrmancini10. The partnership between the Italian coach and Richard Mille are two references (RM 11-01 and RM 11-04) designed especially to meet the manager need. In fact both watches features a flyback chronograph function aimed at timing a football match, while also offering a quick view of recovery and overtime. The RM11-01 was presented in 2013 in titanium and rose gold marking the start of the partnership, while in 2019 its successor RM 11-04 shows the colors of the Italian national team over a carbon TPT® case. This last reference has registered a truly frightening growth on the market, reaching its list price tripling. For the RM 11-01, however, the growth was less important. The European victory brought a lot of attention to these watches, do you think they will still be able to grow? #RichardMille

This post was created in partnership with @watchanalytics

node.text:
Giannis Antetokounmpo of Milwaukee Bucks during the Victory Parade of the 2021 NBA Finals was wearing a @rolex Sky-Dweller in stainless steel with black dial. The Rolex Oyster Perpetual Sky-Dweller was introduced in 2012 and displays the time in two time zones simultaneously and has an annual calendar. The reference time, in 24-hour format, is shown via an off-centre disc, and the local time is read using conventional centre hands. #Rolex 

Retail price: $ 16,550.00
Market price: $ 23,500.00

Photo: @gettyimages | @rolex

A close-up of @purnell_official Escape II movement in motion, the world’s fastest triple-axis tourbillon. The Spherion's inner cage housing the balance wheel makes a full revolution in just 8 seconds, the second cage completes its revolution in 16 seconds, while the outer cage rotates in 30 seconds. #Purnell

Limited edition: 3 pieces 
Retail price: $ 485,000.00

Photo: @joyisabellephoto

node.text:
@memphisdepay of FC Barcelona during his first press conference at Camp Nou was wearing a @rolex Cosmograph Daytona in 18k rose gold with brown ‘chocolate’ dial. This timepiece was added to the collection in 2019 and it features rose gold hour markers and black sub dials. The Daytona is equipped with calibre 4130, a self-winding mechanical chronograph movement developed and manufactured by Rolex. #Rolex

Retail price: $ 39,350.00
Market price: $ 60,000.00

Photo: @fcbarcelona | @rolex
